    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ultimate Penalty</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eugene Netupsky letter disputes October 14 letter opposing death penalty</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The writer of an Oct. 14 letter that called to ''execution duty'' those who support the death penalty should herself first witness a wanton murder of a helpless victim, often pleading to be spared, only to be killed mercilessly.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The writer of an Oct. 14 letter that called to ''execution duty'' those who support the death penalty should herself first witness a wanton murder of a helpless victim, often pleading to be spared, only to be killed mercilessly.</p>
        <p>Only then would the writer begin to understand the voice of the majority.</p>
        <p>EUGENE NETUPSKY  New York, Oct. 15, 2000</p>
      </block>
